Rating: 4
A few friends got together to do a "Chopped Cookoff" party and one of the ingredients was parsnips... Something that totally grossed me out, until I made these potato parsnip latkes. The only thing I changed up a bit, was I pan fried them in a little vegetable oil instead of baking in the oven. Pan fried until they were golden brown on both sides, then moved them to a paper towel to cool. They were absolutely yummy and I'm sure the reason my dish WON the cook off competition.

